Norway ' s Saga quits Indonesian business . Norway ' s Saga Petroleum ASA announced on Friday it was terminating its business in Indonesia because it found it difficult to operate in a cost - effective way in the Asian country . The oil company said it had invested 400 million crowns in Indonesia and that it was now selling its stakes there . " Saga Petroleum will pull out of Indonesia to prioritise its international activities in other areas , " a statement to the Oslo Bourse said . " Saga has weighed a series of business opportunities in the country , but has not found a basis for increasing its investments . The company finds it difficult to operate in a cost - effective manner in Indonesia given the limited scope of its activity there , " the statement said . - - Oslo newsroom + 47 22 42 50 41 
